I have a basically new Sig SP2022 that I am wanting to trade.

I just bought the Sig this month and have only put exactly a 100 rounds through it.  Absolutely nothing wrong with it, I have just had some Springfield XD's in the past and I would really like to get another one as they have all the features I like.

title: For Sale:  4.5 million volt concealed stun gun tactical light
postcontent:
Looking for a new toy? Here's a fun one... it's a functional 160 lumen rechargeable LED tactical flashlight complete with carry case that houses a neat little secret. It's actually a covert 4.5 million volt (4,500,000 V) stun gun. You wouldn't know it by looking at it. There are no visible prongs or anything that would suggest its secondary function. The electrical current actually arcs across the strike bezel on the forward end which is really quite ingenious. The arc is very visible and crackles loud as heck. The sound of the arc alone is enough to make most people think twice, not to mention how visible it is and that's not even counting the 160 lumen tactical light sufficient to temporarily blind someone and devastate their night vision. I for one, would not want to get zapped with it. 

In my opinion, the best use for this thing is as a supplement to your carry gun. If you carry you should have a tactical light on you anyway and this device serves that purpose as well as (depending on the situation) giving you one last practical option beyond a verbal command to potentially deter a would-be-attacker before you have to draw and fire. In my experience most people will turn and run when they see and hear that arc unless they are hell-bent on doing you harm (in which case, don't wait for them to get close enough to use it, go for your gun!)
